JOHANNESBURG - Embattled Ford SA CEO Jeffery Nemeth will be returning to the US.The Ford Motor Company on Tuesday announced the appointment of Toyota executive Casper Kruger as managing director for the Sub-Saharan Africa region, with effect from 1 April.Nemeth was forced to announce the recall of 4,000 Kuga SUVs in South Africa because of critical safety flaws. Some 46 vehicles spontaneously burst into flames and one Ford driver died.READ: Kuga drivers to file class action suit against FordHis return to the US follows reports that South African insurance giants Auto & General and Dialdirect were to take legal action against Ford.The company drew severe criticism for its handling of the Kuga fiasco, prompting the National Consumer Commission to investigate the fires.eNCA